<seg id=1> Chinese insurance industry has initiated a project for supervisory management reform in Beijing </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News agency, Beijing, January 21st-A research project initiated in Beijing days ago. The purposes of this project are to assist the People's Bank of China to supervise and manage insurance laws and regulations that are drawn up for foreign insurance institutions in China; and to explore systems and measures for insurance standardization. </seg>
<seg id=3> The project is funded by British Loyal Sun Insurance Group and American Lincoln National Group and undertaken by American Yongdao Accountant Firm. The total amount of investments equals 1,400,000 US dollars. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> This project of supervisory management in the insurance industry will systematically analyze the foreign insurance companies in China and the current insurance regulations.  Attempting to work out a constructive research proposal by drawing on the experience of other countries for reference.  This will benefit the development of supervisory management in the Chinese insurance industry, and improve and perfect the laws and regulations for supervisory management. </seg>
<seg id=5> This initiated project of the supervisory management in the insurance industry will conduct further research based on the current laws and regulations that are implemented in the foreign insurance institutions under the People's Bank of China, and strive for enhancements of the organized structures and operational management, especially the development of early stage warning systems. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> It was presented that, the new laws and regulations of supervisory management in the insurance industry will improve and perfect the current laws and regulations that are implemented in the foreign insurance institutions in China. Meanwhile, it will also assist the People's Bank of China to enhance their management system of supervising the whole insurance market. </seg>
</p>
